* * @desc * Provides a convenient way to retrieve a single web element or multiple web elements, * so that they can be used with Serenity/JS {@link @serenity-js/core/lib/screenplay~Interaction}s. * * Check out the examples below, as well as the unit tests demonstrating the usage. * * @example Imaginary website under test * *
    *
  • Apple
    • *
  • Banana
    • *
  • Coconut
    • *
  • Date
    • *
*
* Coconut is not available *
* * * * @example Locating a single element * import { by, Target, TargetElement } from '@serenity-js/webdriverio'; * * const proceedToCheckoutButton: TargetElement = * Target.the('Proceed to Checkout button').located(by.css(`button[type='submit']`)); * * @example Locating multiple elements * import { by, Target, TargetElements } from '@serenity-js/webdriverio'; * * const basketItems: TargetElements = * Target.all('items in the basket').located(by.css('ul#basket li')); * * @example Locating element relative to another element * import { by, Target, TargetElement } from '@serenity-js/webdriverio'; * * const summary: TargetElement = * Target.the('summary').located(by.id('message')); * * const outOfStockItem: TargetElement = * Target.the('out of stock item').of(summary).located(by.css('.out-of-stock')) * * @example Filtering elements matched by a locator * import { by, Target, Text } from '@serenity-js/webdriverio'; * import { endsWith } from '@serenity-js/assertions'; * * const basketItems = * Target.all('items in the basket').located(by.css('ul#basket li')) * .where(Text, endsWith('e')); // Apple, Date * * @example Counting items matched by a locator * import { endsWith } from '@serenity-js/assertions'; * import { Question } from '@serenity-js/core'; * import { by, Target, Text } from '@serenity-js/webdriverio'; * * const basketItemsCount: Question> = * Target.all('items in the basket').located(by.css('ul#basket li')) * .count() // 4 * * @example Getting first item matched by a locator * import { Question } from '@serenity-js/core'; * import { by, Target } from '@serenity-js/webdriverio'; * import { Element } from 'webdriverio'; * * const apple: Question>> = * Target.all('items in the basket').located(by.css('ul#basket li')) * .first() * * @example Getting last item matched by a locator * import { Question } from '@serenity-js/core'; * import { by, Target } from '@serenity-js/webdriverio'; * import { endsWith } from '@serenity-js/assertions'; * import { Element } from 'webdriverio'; * * const date: Question>> = * Target.all('items in the basket').located(by.css('ul#basket li')) * .last() * * @example Getting nth item matched by a locator * import { Question } from '@serenity-js/core'; * import { by, Target } from '@serenity-js/webdriverio'; * import { Element } from 'webdriverio'; * * const banana: Question>> = * Target.all('items in the basket').located(by.css('ul#basket li')) * .get(1) * * @example Using multiple filters and nested targets * import { Question } from '@serenity-js/core'; * import { contain, endsWith } from '@serenity-js/assertions'; * import { by, CSSClasses, Target, Text } from '@serenity-js/webdriverio'; * import { Element } from 'webdriverio'; * * class Basket { * static component = Target.the('basket').located(by.id('basket')); * * static items = Target.all('items').located(by.css('li')) * .of(Basket.component); * * static link = Target.the('link').located(by.css('a')); * } * * const date: Question>> = * Basket.items * .where(Text, endsWith('e')) * .where(CSSClasses.of(Basket.link), contain('has-discount')) * .first() * * @example Clicking on an element * import { actorCalled } from '@serenity-js/core'; * import { BrowseTheWeb, Click } from '@serenity-js/webdriverio'; * * actorCalled('Jane') * .whoCan(BrowseTheWeb.using(browser)) * .attemptsTo( * Click.on(proceedToCheckoutButton), * ); * * @example Retrieving text of multiple elements and performing an assertion * import { Ensure, contain } from '@serenity-js/assertions'; * import { actorCalled } from '@serenity-js/core'; * import { BrowseTheWeb, Text } from '@serenity-js/webdriverio'; * * const basketItemNames = Text.ofAll(basketItems); * * actorCalled('Jane') * .whoCan(BrowseTheWeb.using(browser)) * .attemptsTo( * Ensure.that(basketItemNames, contain('Apple')) * ); * * @example Waiting on an element * import { actorCalled } from '@serenity-js/core'; * import { BrowseTheWeb, Wait, isClickable } from '@serenity-js/webdriverio'; * * actorCalled('Jane') * .whoCan(BrowseTheWeb.using(browser)) * .attemptsTo( * Wait.until(proceedToCheckoutButton, isClickable()), * );
